"================ app/README.md ================
# Vendor Onboarding

Approval workflow for onboarding new vendors with 4-eyes review.

Generated by \`@openrupiv/compiler\` from [\`spec.json\`](./spec.json). Do not
edit these files by hand — edit the spec and recompile; the same spec always
produces byte-identical output (ADR-0001).

| | |
|---|---|
| Slug | \`vendor-onboarding\` |
| App version | \`0.1.0\` |
| Spec version | \`0.1\` |
| Roles | \`requester\`, \`reviewer\`, \`compliance\` |

## Contents

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| \`spec.json\` | Canonical app spec — the contract |
| \`migrations/0001_init.sql\` | Database schema (versioned, forward-only) |
| \`package.json\`, \`test/\` | Standalone invariant tests — \`node --test\`, zero dependencies |
| \`server.mjs\` | Optional entry: serve this directory with \`@openrupiv/runtime\` |

## Entities

### Vendor

A company we may do business with.

SQL table: \`vendor\` · API base path: \`/api/vendor\`

| Field | Type | Column | SQL type | Constraints | Default |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| \`name\` | string | \`name\` | \`text\` | required, unique | — |
| \`contactEmail\` | string | \`contact_email\` | \`text\` | required | — |
| \`country\` | string | \`country\` | \`text\` | — | — |
| \`riskTier\` | enum(low, medium, high) | \`risk_tier\` | \`text\` | — | \`"medium"\` |

### VendorApplication

A request to onboard a vendor.

SQL table: \`vendor_application\` · API base path: \`/api/vendor-application\`

| Field | Type | Column | SQL type | Constraints | Default |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| \`vendor\` | reference → Vendor | \`vendor_id\` | \`uuid\` | required | — |
| \`justification\` | text | \`justification\` | \`text\` | required | — |
| \`annualSpend\` | number | \`annual_spend\` | \`double precision\` | — | — |
| \`status\` | enum(draft, submitted, in_review, approved, rejected) | \`status\` | \`text\` | required | \`"draft"\` |

Every entity table also carries \`id uuid\` (primary key), \`created_at\`, and
\`updated_at\` — set by the database, never by clients.

## Workflows

### \`vendor-approval\` — VendorApplication.status

State machine on \`VendorApplication.status\`; initial state \`draft\`.
The \`status\` field is read-only through the create/update API:
the server sets the initial value on create, and the transitions below are
the only writer.

\`\`\`
[*] --> draft
draft --submit--> submitted   [roles: requester]
submitted --start-review--> in_review   [roles: reviewer]
in_review --approve--> approved   [roles: reviewer, compliance] [2 distinct approvers]
in_review --reject--> rejected   [roles: reviewer, compliance]
\`\`\`

| Transition | From | To | Guard roles | Guard predicates | Approvals required |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| \`submit\` | \`draft\` | \`submitted\` | \`requester\` | — | — |
| \`start-review\` | \`submitted\` | \`in_review\` | \`reviewer\` | — | — |
| \`approve\` | \`in_review\` | \`approved\` | \`reviewer\`, \`compliance\` | — | 2 distinct approvers (\`reviewer\`, \`compliance\`) |
| \`reject\` | \`in_review\` | \`rejected\` | \`reviewer\`, \`compliance\` | — | — |

## Pages

| Page | Route | Type | Entity | Title | Fields |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| \`vendors\` | \`/p/vendors\` | list | Vendor | Vendors | all fields |
| \`vendor-form\` | \`/p/vendor-form\` | form | Vendor | New vendor | all fields |
| \`applications\` | \`/p/applications\` | list | VendorApplication | Applications | \`vendor\`, \`status\`, \`annualSpend\` |
| \`application-detail\` | \`/p/application-detail\` | detail | VendorApplication | Application | all fields |
| \`application-form\` | \`/p/application-form\` | form | VendorApplication | New application | \`vendor\`, \`justification\`, \`annualSpend\` |

## HTTP routes

Served by \`@openrupiv/runtime\`. Every route requires an authenticated OIDC
session except \`/healthz\`, \`/auth/login\`, and \`/auth/callback\`. There is no
DELETE in v0. Workflow state fields cannot be written through create/update.

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| GET | \`/healthz\` | Liveness probe (no auth) |
| GET | \`/auth/login\` | Start OIDC login (Authorization Code + PKCE) |
| GET | \`/auth/callback\` | OIDC redirect target; establishes the session |
| POST | \`/auth/logout\` | Destroy the session |
| GET | \`/\` | Index of pages |
| GET | \`/api/vendor\` | List Vendor records |
| POST | \`/api/vendor\` | Create a Vendor |
| GET | \`/api/vendor/:id\` | Fetch one Vendor |
| PUT | \`/api/vendor/:id\` | Update a Vendor |
| GET | \`/api/vendor-application\` | List VendorApplication records |
| POST | \`/api/vendor-application\` | Create a VendorApplication |
| GET | \`/api/vendor-application/:id\` | Fetch one VendorApplication |
| PUT | \`/api/vendor-application/:id\` | Update a VendorApplication |
| POST | \`/api/vendor-application/:id/transitions/submit\` | Fire \`submit\` (draft → submitted) |
| POST | \`/api/vendor-application/:id/transitions/start-review\` | Fire \`start-review\` (submitted → in_review) |
| POST | \`/api/vendor-application/:id/transitions/approve\` | Fire \`approve\` (in_review → approved) |
| POST | \`/api/vendor-application/:id/transitions/reject\` | Fire \`reject\` (in_review → rejected) |
| GET | \`/p/vendors\` | Page \`vendors\` (list of Vendor) |
| GET | \`/p/vendor-form\` | Page \`vendor-form\` (form of Vendor) |
| GET | \`/p/applications\` | Page \`applications\` (list of VendorApplication) |
| GET | \`/p/application-detail\` | Page \`application-detail\` (detail of VendorApplication) |
| GET | \`/p/application-form\` | Page \`application-form\` (form of VendorApplication) |

Transition endpoints respond \`{ "status": "pending", "approvals": k, "required": n }\`
while approvals are outstanding and \`{ "status": "transitioned", "state": "<to>" }\` on
completion. Failures: 403 \`ERR_FORBIDDEN_ROLE\`; 409 \`ERR_BAD_STATE\`,
\`ERR_GUARD_FAILED\`, or \`ERR_DUPLICATE_APPROVER\` (the same user may not
approve twice — approvals must come from distinct authenticated users).

## Running this app

- **Tests** (zero installs, Node ≥ 20): \`node --test\`
- **Serve with the runtime library:** install \`@openrupiv/runtime\`, then
  \`node server.mjs\`. Configuration comes from the environment:
  \`DATABASE_URL\`, \`OIDC_ISSUER\`, \`OIDC_CLIENT_ID\`, \`OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET\`,
  \`SESSION_SECRET\`, \`BASE_URL\`. Authentication is OIDC only — there is no
  local-password mode (ADR-0003).
- **Or via the workspace Compose stack:** \`docker compose up\` from the
  workspace root (bundles Postgres and a dev-only Dex IdP, ADR-0002).

================ app/migrations/0001_init.sql ================
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pgcrypto;

-- Migration 0001_init for app "vendor-onboarding" v0.1.0 (spec v0.1).
-- Generated by @openrupiv/compiler as a deterministic projection of app/spec.json.
-- Forward-only: never edit a migration after it has been applied; add a new one.

CREATE TABLE vendor (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name text NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  contact_email text NOT NULL,
  country text,
  risk_tier text DEFAULT 'medium' CHECK (risk_tier IN ('low', 'medium', 'high')),
  created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE TABLE vendor_application (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  vendor_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES vendor(id),
  justification text NOT NULL,
  annual_spend double precision,
  status text NOT NULL DEFAULT 'draft' CHECK (status IN ('draft', 'submitted', 'in_review', 'approved', 'rejected')),
  created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

